prediction: Forced to rest at Nicomedia, he was baptized there, and died.
constantine i fake donation revealed by lorenzo valla

The famous 'Donation of Constantine'  (with which the emperor was supposed to have Given Pope Sylvester I primacy over Antioch, Constantinople, Alexandria, and Jerusalem, and political control of Italy, and made the Pope supreme judge of the clergy)  was in fact an 8th-century forgery from the reign of Charlemagne, as proved in the 15th century by the humanist scholar Valla.
Although Constantine had originally hoped to be baptized in the Jordan River, the ceremony was delayed until the end of his life.
He fell ill at Helenopolis in 337, while preparing for a campaign against Persia, and, realizing the seriousness of his condition, he attempted to return to Constantinople.
